In a statement released on Wednesday, The Shoprite Group has condemned violence and intimidation of Nigerians and other African nationals in South Africa. Shoprite expressed disapproval over the ongoing acts of violence in South Africa and “intolerance being levelled against South Africans living in Nigeria”.  The post Shoprite Nigeria condemns Xenophobic Violence Source: Bella Naija By Rasheed Sobowale South African retail store in Nigeria, Shoprite, has condemned in its entirety, the xenophobic attack in its country home against Nigerians. A release by Shoprite, made available to Vanguard title: SHOPRITE NIGERIA SPEAKS OUT AGAINST XENOPHOBIA, categorically condemned the move, saying “In the light of recent attacks… September 4, 2019 In "News" In the light of recent attacks on other Africans especially, Nigerians living in South Africa; Shoprite Nigeria in strong terms wishes to condemn any kind of xenophobic violence and intimidation against the citizens of other countries, anywhere in the world. Continue reading Breaking: Shoprite Nigeria speaks out against Xenophobia at… September 4, 2019 In "News" Some protesters on Tuesday attacked Shoprite in Circle Mall, Lekki, a South African establishment. The protest is in response to the xenophobic attacks on Nigerians in South Africa. It was reported that some youth invaded the shopping mall, destroyed properties before the police arrived. The xenophobic attacks have been condemned… September 3, 2019 In "Entertainment"